298
00:20:44,130 --> 00:20:45,980
Why don't you revolt against Qing to restore Ming dynasty?

299
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:46,760
Childish.

300
00:20:48,660 --> 00:20:49,460
Here, Kai.

301
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:50,770
I've had enough.

302
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:53,290
I'm done.

303
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:56,690
Childish!

304
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:09,360
Don't be angry. Let's eat.

305
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:14,180
Here.

306
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,880
What are schools

307
00:21:15,930 --> 00:21:17,590
teaching students nowadays?

308
00:21:18,030 --> 00:21:18,830
Take it easy.

309
00:21:41,630 --> 00:21:43,590
I always thought humans are fickle

310
00:21:45,670 --> 00:21:47,470
but eating habits don't change.

311
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,600
I guess not.

312
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:53,980
Haven't I been eating?

313
00:21:55,870 --> 00:21:57,130
Eat as much as you want.

314
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,580
A Japanese friend went back to Japan,

315
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:36,910
so he entrusted me with his house.

316
00:22:38,910 --> 00:22:40,310
Someone has to live in it.

317
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:43,290
So I need a favor.

318
00:22:44,150 --> 00:22:44,720
No.

319
00:22:45,390 --> 00:22:46,920
Ms. Guan, I really can't.

320
00:22:48,670 --> 00:22:50,320
You can rent this house out.

321
00:22:51,510 --> 00:22:52,790
Didn't you say

322
00:22:52,990 --> 00:22:54,390
you're under my control?

323
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:01,800
Ms. Guan.

324
00:23:02,290 --> 00:23:03,160
Mr. Song.

325
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,490
Aunt Chang's

326
00:23:04,580 --> 00:23:06,510
been with me for almost four years.

327
00:23:06,980 --> 00:23:09,440
She'll take care of your household affairs.

328
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:12,060
Her fried pork's really authentic.

329
00:23:27,820 --> 00:23:29,420
I want to help.

330
00:23:29,820 --> 00:23:30,940
But if I live here,

331
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:32,830
I'd be a freeloader.

332
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:35,650
I won't force you.

333
00:23:36,660 --> 00:23:38,260
But don't reject me just yet.

334
00:23:46,850 --> 00:23:47,850
Just open it.

335
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:51,700
Let's talk business.

336
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:53,300
Yes.

337
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:57,630
Forget about the hospital.

338
00:23:58,220 --> 00:23:59,620
We must've lost the lead.

339
00:24:01,630 --> 00:24:03,770
Go interrogate Shi with Ding Peng.

340
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:05,280
Will it work?

341
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,110
It's up to you.

342
00:24:08,310 --> 00:24:09,370
If it doesn't work,

343
00:24:09,710 --> 00:24:11,200
deal with him.

344
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:12,940
How?

345
00:24:14,250 --> 00:24:15,300
Two options.

346
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:18,840
One is to shoot him to death.

347
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:22,220
Do we do it?

348
00:24:28,110 --> 00:24:29,400
It's a rite of passage

349
00:24:30,430 --> 00:24:31,910
for new special agents.

350
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,930
What's the second option?

351
00:24:49,930 --> 00:24:51,550
The Japanese will handle it.

352
00:24:51,890 --> 00:24:53,610
It's none of our business

353
00:24:54,750 --> 00:24:56,030
how they do it.

354
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:57,620
Nice?

355
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:02,680
Aunt Chang!

356
00:25:04,110 --> 00:25:05,720
Help me pack these.

357
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:06,950
I'm taking them away.

358
00:25:18,030 --> 00:25:19,310
Hu Bin is

359
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:23,510
someone who needs to be

360
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:24,720
humbled.

361
00:25:27,010 --> 00:25:28,670
Don't hold back because of me.

362
00:25:29,150 --> 00:25:30,240
Teach him a lesson

363
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:32,860
and you'll have an easy time here.

364
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:36,220
Having blood on your hands gives you a hostile aura

365
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:38,410
that toughens you up.

366
00:25:40,430 --> 00:25:40,950
Got it.

367
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:28,850
I have good news for you.

368
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,530
Your wife's given birth.

369
00:26:33,430 --> 00:26:34,290
I know.

370
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:37,600
How did you know?

371
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:40,910
I heard the baby crying.

372
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,510
Just now too.

373
00:26:43,580 --> 00:26:46,180
Now it's probably asleep after drinking milk.

374
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:47,880
Enough small talk.

375
00:26:56,450 --> 00:27:00,690
I can even hear its breathing clearly.

376
00:27:01,510 --> 00:27:02,670
Familial ties

377
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:06,270
are the hardest to sever.

378
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:10,040
Siblings,

379
00:27:11,610 --> 00:27:12,690
father and child,

380
00:27:14,060 --> 00:27:15,220
husband and wife.

381
00:27:23,310 --> 00:27:24,510
Did it cross your mind

382
00:27:24,900 --> 00:27:26,200
that if you're gone,

383
00:27:27,470 --> 00:27:29,720
they'll lose their last hope?

384
00:27:30,750 --> 00:27:32,110
Your baby's born

385
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:35,000
into a life of suffering.

386
00:27:35,470 --> 00:27:36,870
Whose words are those?

387
00:27:37,830 --> 00:27:39,230
It's unlike you.

388
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:46,040
Then teach me

389
00:27:47,990 --> 00:27:49,590
what I should say.

390
00:27:51,190 --> 00:27:52,750
You pounced on

391
00:27:53,390 --> 00:27:55,100
that Japanese at the platform

392
00:27:55,930 --> 00:27:58,350
to save that female agent, right?

393
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:02,440
Many people closer to her

394
00:28:02,670 --> 00:28:03,910
didn't do that.

395
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:05,590
Why?

396
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:11,650
Listen to me.

397
00:28:13,290 --> 00:28:14,510
Leave here.

398
00:28:15,310 --> 00:28:16,110
Although

399
00:28:16,790 --> 00:28:19,250
you look imposing in this uniform,

400
00:28:20,010 --> 00:28:21,770
you can't wear anything less.

401
00:28:23,020 --> 00:28:24,220
Like suits.

402
00:28:28,780 --> 00:28:30,670
In those Japanese riding boots,

403
00:28:31,780 --> 00:28:32,440
you

404
00:28:33,310 --> 00:28:34,260
might feel

405
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:35,540
domineering.

406
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:36,120
Right?

407
00:28:37,450 --> 00:28:38,860
Why don't you try

408
00:28:39,110 --> 00:28:41,570
English Crockett leather shoes?

409
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:49,040
You don't have to sell your soul.

410
00:28:49,110 --> 00:28:50,630
You can just pay for them.

411
00:28:51,120 --> 00:28:51,930
Young man.

412
00:28:52,900 --> 00:28:53,900
Think

413
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:55,830
about what I said.

414
00:29:05,390 --> 00:29:06,070
Cruel.

415
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,440
So cruel.

416
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,950
You can even forsake your kid.

417
00:29:18,230 --> 00:29:20,100
How did they brainwash you

418
00:29:20,870 --> 00:29:22,470
to make you so cold-hearted?

419
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:24,200
As a doctor,

420
00:29:25,070 --> 00:29:27,130
you could've lived a dignified life.

421
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:28,680
Dignity?

422
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:34,610
Dignity and faith are two different things.

423
00:30:17,430 --> 00:30:18,310
Zhuowen.

424
00:30:21,470 --> 00:30:23,070
Check out the purchase list.

425
00:30:24,590 --> 00:30:26,250
Get the money from Accounting

426
00:30:26,470 --> 00:30:28,460
after the budget's approved by Ms. Guan.

427
00:30:28,460 --> 00:30:29,660
Then get a car

428
00:30:29,690 --> 00:30:31,210
and everything ready

429
00:30:31,230 --> 00:30:32,360
as soon as possible.

430
00:30:32,860 --> 00:30:33,620
I'd have to

431
00:30:34,510 --> 00:30:35,470
explore all of Harbin

432
00:30:35,470 --> 00:30:36,790
to get everything.

433
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:38,310
Cut the crap. Go now.

434
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:44,760
Come in.

435
00:30:49,490 --> 00:30:50,190
Ms. Guan.

436
00:30:50,420 --> 00:30:52,880
Mr. Jin asked me to give you last month's receipt.

437
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:54,620
He needs your signature.

438
00:31:02,700 --> 00:31:03,330
Ms. Guan!

439
00:31:03,510 --> 00:31:05,170
Squirrel-encoded telegram!

440
00:31:35,110 --> 00:31:36,110
Never mention...

441
00:31:39,020 --> 00:31:39,830
an encoded telegram

442
00:31:39,830 --> 00:31:41,360
when there's a third party.

443
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:44,670
Why don't you

444
00:31:44,790 --> 00:31:46,400
use a megaphone?

445
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:50,510
You'll be confined from tomorrow.

446
00:31:50,510 --> 00:31:51,100
Yes.

447
00:31:54,070 --> 00:31:54,670
Ms. Guan.

448
00:31:55,210 --> 00:31:56,090
I'll get going.

449
00:31:57,310 --> 00:31:58,110
Wait.

450
00:32:00,270 --> 00:32:01,130
Another thing.

451
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,430
Watch Pan Yue

452
00:32:08,590 --> 00:32:09,660
and Hu Bin.

453
00:32:11,450 --> 00:32:12,890
Report to me directly.

454
00:32:14,190 --> 00:32:15,230
Why them?

455
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:17,520
Where do I sign?

456
00:32:22,780 --> 00:32:23,380
Here.

457
00:32:25,100 --> 00:32:27,510
They've been here for a long time.

458
00:32:28,710 --> 00:32:29,520
Veterans

459
00:32:29,780 --> 00:32:31,180
consider their options.

460
00:32:33,490 --> 00:32:35,090
How much authority do I have?

461
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:38,930
The highest authority.

462
00:32:39,470 --> 00:32:40,270
Including

463
00:32:40,750 --> 00:32:41,900
looking into you?

464
00:32:45,590 --> 00:32:47,190
Did I ask the wrong question?

465
00:32:53,380 --> 00:32:55,020
You know what to do.

466
00:33:00,790 --> 00:33:01,430
Got it.

467
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:18,340
[There's a mole]

468
00:33:52,370 --> 00:33:53,200
Let's go.

469
00:33:56,030 --> 00:33:58,820
[Budget Application]

470
00:34:00,470 --> 00:34:02,070
Who used to buy these things?

471
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:04,310
Mr. Jin himself.

472
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:10,300
How much commission does he get?

473
00:34:14,380 --> 00:34:15,179
This much?

474
00:34:15,909 --> 00:34:17,540
No, not that much.

475
00:34:18,139 --> 00:34:19,739
Just enough for cigarettes.

476
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:28,010
He ate the meat and you had leftover soup.

477
00:34:28,010 --> 00:34:29,130
New rules.

478
00:34:29,710 --> 00:34:31,310
Let's all have meat and soup.

479
00:34:33,210 --> 00:34:34,650
You'll get a fat check

480
00:34:35,380 --> 00:34:36,699
once you get it done.

481
00:34:38,210 --> 00:34:39,010
Okay.

482
00:34:40,170 --> 00:34:41,100
Pull over there.

483
00:34:45,070 --> 00:34:46,230
Okay, stop here.

484
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,449
I'll leave this task to you.

485
00:34:53,870 --> 00:34:55,400
Wait for me here after that.

486
00:34:59,350 --> 00:35:00,480
You must wait for me.

487
00:35:02,910 --> 00:35:03,420
Right!

488
00:35:03,450 --> 00:35:04,810
We've to return by noon!

489
00:35:23,980 --> 00:35:27,280
[Men's Restroom]

490
00:35:26,230 --> 00:35:26,890
Stop there.

491
00:35:46,180 --> 00:35:46,710
Ms. Guan.

492
00:35:46,950 --> 00:35:47,950
Wu's awake.

493
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,370
He recalled that

494
00:35:52,250 --> 00:35:53,650
the person who shot him

495
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:55,230
was in a checkered suit.

496
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,800
The suited man

497
00:35:57,830 --> 00:35:59,070
is either a communist

498
00:35:59,830 --> 00:36:01,760
or a Japanese Secret Police agent.

499
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:05,910
Regardless,

500
00:36:07,270 --> 00:36:09,430
he must be in cahoots with Shi.

501
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:21,280
I’ll ask Hu Bin to wait for you at the train station.

502
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:22,500
Find him.

503
00:36:24,230 --> 00:36:25,960
Yes, I'll find him.

504
00:37:03,510 --> 00:37:04,180
Wu.

505
00:37:05,430 --> 00:37:07,850
Are you sure the one who shot you

506
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,540
was in a checkered suit?

507
00:37:12,390 --> 00:37:13,020
Yes.

508
00:37:14,750 --> 00:37:15,750
In his thirties

509
00:37:16,450 --> 00:37:18,010
and cultured-looking?

510
00:37:28,390 --> 00:37:30,190
The mantis preying on the cicada

511
00:37:30,940 --> 00:37:33,190
fails to see the oriole preying on it.

512
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:36,860
Interesting.

513
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:39,490
Get well soon!

514
00:37:52,350 --> 00:37:53,060
You!

515
00:37:53,390 --> 00:37:53,990
Come here.

516
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:57,490
Mr. Hu.

517
00:37:58,080 --> 00:37:59,080
What's your name?

518
00:37:59,190 --> 00:37:59,890
Ding Peng.

519
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,770
Fine, whatever.

520
00:38:02,230 --> 00:38:03,710
Weren't you with Zhuowen?

521
00:38:03,710 --> 00:38:04,370
Where is he?

522
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:06,530
Running errands. Shopping.

523
00:38:08,190 --> 00:38:09,480
Are you that honest?

524
00:38:11,110 --> 00:38:13,440
You don't mind others taking your credit?

525
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:17,820
Remember, you're as good as anyone.

526
00:38:20,110 --> 00:38:21,070
Come with me.

527
00:38:29,300 --> 00:38:30,840
Use your brain.

528
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:32,980
Get the equipment.

529
00:38:33,990 --> 00:38:34,650
Equipment.

530
00:38:42,190 --> 00:38:44,200
[Harbin Station]

531
00:38:47,070 --> 00:38:48,510
27th?

532
00:38:48,650 --> 00:38:50,880
When someone was shot at the station?

533
00:38:52,140 --> 00:38:53,540
Yes, that day.

534
00:38:53,790 --> 00:38:54,390
Yes.

535
00:38:54,410 --> 00:38:55,210
It's the 27th.

536
00:38:56,110 --> 00:38:57,510
It was crowded and messy.

537
00:38:57,540 --> 00:38:59,000
My cousin hasn't come home

538
00:38:59,220 --> 00:39:00,480
since he disappeared.

539
00:39:00,620 --> 00:39:01,980
Help me out.

540
00:39:02,460 --> 00:39:04,140
He's a bit shorter than me,

541
00:39:04,580 --> 00:39:05,950
in a checkered suit

542
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,860
and black and white leather shoes.

543
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:08,470
No idea.

544
00:39:08,590 --> 00:39:09,610
He left the station

545
00:39:09,610 --> 00:39:10,460
around noon.

546
00:39:11,770 --> 00:39:13,920
He limps on his right leg?

547
00:39:15,990 --> 00:39:17,590
He doesn't walk well indeed.

548
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:19,340
He refused to

549
00:39:19,510 --> 00:39:20,310
take my cart.

550
00:39:20,340 --> 00:39:22,220
He said I'm old and slow.

551
00:39:22,250 --> 00:39:23,380
He took Shun’s cart.

552
00:39:23,830 --> 00:39:24,350
Shun?

553
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:26,570
-Shun went home.
-Who's Shun?

554
00:39:27,550 --> 00:39:28,640
To take care

555
00:39:28,670 --> 00:39:29,630
of his sick mom.

556
00:39:29,660 --> 00:39:30,790
When will he be back?

557
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:33,670
No idea.

558
00:39:33,690 --> 00:39:34,340
No idea.

559
00:39:34,990 --> 00:39:35,770
Did he talk

560
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,170
about that trip he made?

561
00:39:37,390 --> 00:39:39,310
Yes, he said it was good.

562
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:40,190
How?

563
00:39:42,030 --> 00:39:44,390
At Daduchuan Street's intersection,

564
00:39:44,680 --> 00:39:46,150
he was told to stop.

565
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:47,890
It wasn't even halfway

566
00:39:48,130 --> 00:39:49,300
but he paid in full.

567
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:50,640
Then Shun came back.

568
00:39:51,270 --> 00:39:53,000
Where was he originally going?

569
00:39:54,270 --> 00:39:55,150
He didn't say.

570
00:39:55,830 --> 00:39:57,080
No idea.

571
00:39:57,370 --> 00:39:58,900
Get me to Daduchuan Street.

572
00:39:59,310 --> 00:40:00,950
Sir, here!

573
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:05,110
Be careful.

574
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:06,450
Sit tight.

575
00:40:13,710 --> 00:40:16,800
[Daduchuan Street]

576
00:40:18,020 --> 00:40:18,830
We're here.

577
00:40:30,210 --> 00:40:32,130
The cart was stopped here.

578
00:40:33,170 --> 00:40:34,640
Why did that suited man

579
00:40:34,860 --> 00:40:36,100
suddenly stop?

580
00:40:37,830 --> 00:40:39,430
He must've seen

581
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,620
or thought of something.

582
00:40:53,250 --> 00:40:55,250
He limps on his right leg?

583
00:40:57,550 --> 00:40:59,410
He doesn't walk very well indeed.

584
00:41:08,370 --> 00:41:11,670
[Liu's Orthopedic Massage]
